cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with health-related social media mining using machine learning techniques. The focus is on text classification using recurrent neural networks (RNN) and long short-term memory (LSTM) based embedding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for mining social media data, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms for classification makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with health-related data, which could make cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a relevant sub-category.
